atmfM4MIB.description: This MIB module is the SNMP version of the ATM Forum's M4 interface (network element view).

atmfM4NeVendor.name: atmfM4NeVendor
atmfM4NeVendor.description: The vendor of the ATM network element.

atmfM4NeVersion.name: atmfM4NeVersion
atmfM4NeVersion.description: The version of the ATM network element.

atmfM4NeStartTime.name: atmfM4NeStartTime
atmfM4NeStartTime.description: The time at which the agent was last started; in other words, the time at which sysUpTime was zero.

atmfM4NeAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4NeAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4NeAlarmSeverityIndex.description: An index into the alarm severity profile table, specifying the severity assignments for M4 alarms reported for the ATM network element. The default value for this object is zero.

atmfM4NeSuppressZeroStats.name: atmfM4NeSuppressZeroStats
atmfM4NeSuppressZeroStats.description: When the value of this object is true, no entry will be created in any of the historical statistics tables for intervals in which all counts are zero. The default value for this object is true(1).

atmfM4PhysPathTpTable.name: atmfM4PhysPathTpTable
atmfM4PhysPathTpTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 interface Configuration table extensions for the physical path termination point.

atmfM4PhysPathTpEntry.name: atmfM4PhysPathTpEntry
atmfM4PhysPathTpEntry.description: Columns conceptually added to the interface table entry for an ATM interface to model the physical path termination point. The row of the interface table modeling this object should also include columns for the TC Adapter object and the ATM interface table defined in RFC 1695. The interface table entry for the physical path TP fields of an ATM interface are set up without management system control (or else that setup is outside the scope of M4).

atmfM4PhysPathTpHwUnitIndex.name: atmfM4PhysPathTpHwUnitIndex
atmfM4PhysPathTpHwUnitIndex.description: Specifies the index of the entry in the entPhysicalTable that represents the device (i.e., card) on which the physical path terminates.

atmfM4PhysPathTpPortID.name: atmfM4PhysPathTpPortID
atmfM4PhysPathTpPortID.description: Identifies the port (within the card identified by the hardware unit index) on which the physical path terminates.

atmfM4PhysPathTpAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4PhysPathTpAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4PhysPathTpAlarmSeverityIndex.description: Specifies the index of the entry in the communications alarm severity profile table that should be used. The default value of this object is zero.

atmfM4TcAdapterTable.name: atmfM4TcAdapterTable
atmfM4TcAdapterTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 interface Configuration table extensions for the TC Adapter.

atmfM4TcAdapterEntry.name: atmfM4TcAdapterEntry
atmfM4TcAdapterEntry.description: Columns conceptually added to the interface table entry for an ATM interface to model the TC Adapter. The row of the interface table modeling this object should also include columns for the physical path TP and the ATM interface table defined in RFC 1695. The interface table entry for the TC Adapter fields of an ATM interface are set up without management system control (or else that setup is outside the scope of M4).

atmfM4TcACellScrambling.name: atmfM4TcACellScrambling
atmfM4TcACellScrambling.description: This attribute is used by the management system to activate and deactivate the ATM cell scrambling function. When the value of this attribute is TRUE, cell scrambling on the interface is activated. This attribute shall be present only for interfaces that support the deactivation of cell scrambling. The ATM Forum UNI specification requires cell scrambling for ATM/SONET interfaces but allows cell scrambling to be controlled (i.e., turned on and off) for ATM/DS3 interfaces. The default value of this object is true(1).

atmfM4TcAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4TcAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4TcAlarmSeverityIndex.description: Specifies the index of the entry in the communications alarm severity profile table that should be used. The default value of this object is zero.

atmfM4AtmLayerTable.name: atmfM4AtmLayerTable
atmfM4AtmLayerTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 interface Configuration table extensions for the ATM cell layer.

atmfM4AtmLayerEntry.name: atmfM4AtmLayerEntry
atmfM4AtmLayerEntry.description: Columns conceptually added to the interface table entry for an ATM interface to model the ATM cell layer. The row of the interface table modeling this object should also include columns for the physical path TP and TC Adapter object, as well as the ATM interface table defined in RFC 1695. The default configuration of an entry in this table is used whenever the entries for the physical path TP, etc., are created. The management system configures a UNI, B-ICI, or B-ISSI on the interface by first modifying the atmfM4IfType column (this can be done in the same SNMP set-request that sets up the other necessary variables.

atmfM4IfType.name: atmfM4IfType
atmfM4IfType.description: Specifies the type of ATM cell layer interface defined on the physical path termination point modeled by this entry in the interface table. The default value of this object is none(0).

atmfM4IfLoopbackLocationCode.name: atmfM4IfLoopbackLocationCode
atmfM4IfLoopbackLocationCode.description: Specifies the code that shall exist in incoming OAM Loopback cells that are to be looped back at this interface. A value of zero shall indicate that the management system has not set any loopback location code for this interface. Therefore, zero should not be used as the actual loopback location code for any interface. This object shall be present only for table entries that represent an actual ATM cell layer interface (i.e., the atmfM4IfType is not none(0)). The default value of this object is zero.

atmfM4IfSubscriberAddress.name: atmfM4IfSubscriberAddress
atmfM4IfSubscriberAddress.description: Specifies the address or newline-delimited list of addresses assigned to the UNI. This object shall be present only for table entries that represent a UNI interface. The default value of this object is the null string.

atmfM4IfPreferredCarrier.name: atmfM4IfPreferredCarrier
atmfM4IfPreferredCarrier.description: Specifies the name of the default carrier to use when one is not explicitly identified in the call set-up message. This object shall be present only for table entries that represent a UNI interface and only when SVC services are supported. The default value of this object is the null string.

atmfM4IfFarEndCarrierNetwork.name: atmfM4IfFarEndCarrierNetwork
atmfM4IfFarEndCarrierNetwork.description: Specifies the adjacent carrier to which the B-ICI transmission path is connected. This object shall be present only for table entries that represent a B-ICI interface and only when SVC services are supported. The default value of this object is the null string.

atmfM4VplTable.name: atmfM4VplTable
atmfM4VplTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VPL Termination Point Configuration table extensions. This table augments the VPL configuration table in RFC 1695.

atmfM4VplEntry.name: atmfM4VplEntry
atmfM4VplEntry.description: Additional columns for the VPL configuration table entry.

atmfM4VplSegEndPt.name: atmfM4VplSegEndPt
atmfM4VplSegEndPt.description: Specifies whether the VPL termination point is a segment end-point.

atmfM4VclTable.name: atmfM4VclTable
atmfM4VclTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VCL Termination Point Configuration table extensions. This table augments the VCL configuration table in RFC 1695.

atmfM4VclEntry.name: atmfM4VclEntry
atmfM4VclEntry.description: Additional columns for the VCL configuration table entry.

atmfM4VclSegEndPt.name: atmfM4VclSegEndPt
atmfM4VclSegEndPt.description: Specifies whether the VCL termination point is a segment end-point.

atmfM4VpXConnTable.name: atmfM4VpXConnTable
atmfM4VpXConnTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VP Cross-Connect Configuration table extensions. This table augments the VP Cross-Connect configuration table in RFC 1695.

atmfM4VpXConnEntry.name: atmfM4VpXConnEntry
atmfM4VpXConnEntry.description: Additional columns for the VP Cross-Connect table entry.

atmfM4VpXConnRecover.name: atmfM4VpXConnRecover
atmfM4VpXConnRecover.description: If FALSE, this cross-connection will be removed on failure.

atmfM4VcXConnTable.name: atmfM4VcXConnTable
atmfM4VcXConnTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VC Cross-Connect Configuration table extensions. This table augments the VC Cross-Connect configuration table in RFC 1695.

atmfM4VcXConnEntry.name: atmfM4VcXConnEntry
atmfM4VcXConnEntry.description: Additional columns for the VC Cross-Connect table entry.

atmfM4VcXConnRecover.name: atmfM4VcXConnRecover
atmfM4VcXConnRecover.description: If FALSE, this cross-connection will be removed on failure.

atmfM4VpNextVpiTable.name: atmfM4VpNextVpiTable
atmfM4VpNextVpiTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VP Next VPI value table. This optional table supplies unused VPI values for use in creating entries in the atmVplTable.

atmfM4VpNextVpiEntry.name: atmfM4VpNextVpiEntry
atmfM4VpNextVpiEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents the 'next' VPI value available for a given ATM interface. Each ATM interface (UNI, BICI, BISSI) automatically has an entry in this table associated with it.

atmfM4VpNextVpiValue.name: atmfM4VpNextVpiValue
atmfM4VpNextVpiValue.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for atmVplVpi when creating entries in the atmVplTable. The value -1 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the atmVplVpi value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index (or -1).

atmfM4VcNextVciTable.name: atmfM4VcNextVciTable
atmfM4VcNextVciTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VC Next VCI value table. This optional table supplies unused VCI values for use in creating entries in the atmVclTable.

atmfM4VcNextVciEntry.name: atmfM4VcNextVciEntry
atmfM4VcNextVciEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents the 'next' VCI value available for a given ATM interface. Each VPL Termination Point automatically has an entry in this table associated with it.

atmfM4VcNextVciValue.name: atmfM4VcNextVciValue
atmfM4VcNextVciValue.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for atmVclVci when creating entries in the atmVclTable. The value -1 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the atmVclVci value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index (or -1).

atmfM4CellProtoCurrTable.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrTable
atmfM4CellProtoCurrTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring Current Data table. This table maintains per-interface statistics for the fifteen-minute interval currently being collected.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrEntry.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrEntry
atmfM4CellProtoCurrEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring Current Data table. Each ATM interface (UNI, BICI, BISSI) automatically has an entry in this table associated with it.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrSuspect.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrSuspect
atmfM4CellProtoCurrSuspect.description: If true, the statistics in this entry may be unreliable.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrElapsedTime.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrElapsedTime
atmfM4CellProtoCurrElapsedTime.description: Amount of time, measured in units of 0.01 second, that statistics for this entry (the current interval) have been counted.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrSupprIntvls.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrSupprIntvls
atmfM4CellProtoCurrSupprIntvls.description: This attribute is non-zero only if the ATM NE is suppressing ATM Cell Protocol Monitoring History Data entry creation when the current interval terminates with 'all-zeroes' performance measurements. When non-zero, this attribute represents the number of 'all-zeroes' intervals that were suppressed immediately prior to the current interval. Note that the suppression of 'all-zeroes' intervals is controlled by the atmfM4NeSuppressZeroStats object.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrProtoErrors.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrProtoErrors
atmfM4CellProtoCurrProtoErrors.description: The number of ATM cells dropped on this interface, due to an unrecognized field or set of fields in the ATM cell header, since the start of this interval.

atmfM4CellProtoCurrInOAMCells.name: atmfM4CellProtoCurrInOAMCells
atmfM4CellProtoCurrInOAMCells.description: The number of OAM cells received at this interface since the start of this interval.

atmfM4CellProtoHistTable.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistTable
atmfM4CellProtoHistTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring History Data table. This table maintains per-interface statistics for previous fifteen-minute intervals.

atmfM4CellProtoHistEntry.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistEntry
atmfM4CellProtoHistEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring History Data table. Each ATM interface (UNI, BICI, BISSI) automatically has an entry in this table associated with it for each fifteen- minute interval in which statistics are collected for it.

atmfM4CellProtoHistIndex.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistIndex
atmfM4CellProtoHistIndex.description: A number between 1 and 96, which identifies the interval for which the set of statistics in this entry was collected. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1.

atmfM4CellProtoHistSuspect.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistSuspect
atmfM4CellProtoHistSuspect.description: If true, the statistics in this entry may be unreliable.

atmfM4CellProtoHistElapsedTime.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistElapsedTime

atmfM4CellProtoHistSupprIntvls.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistSupprIntvls

atmfM4CellProtoHistProtoErrors.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistProtoErrors
atmfM4CellProtoHistProtoErrors.description: The number of ATM cells dropped on this interface, due to an unrecognized field or set of fields in the ATM cell header, during this interval.

atmfM4CellProtoHistInOAMCells.name: atmfM4CellProtoHistInOAMCells
atmfM4CellProtoHistInOAMCells.description: The number of OAM cells received at this interface during this interval.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorTable.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorTable
atmfM4CellProtoErrorTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring Error Log table. This table maintains a record of the last error of each type encountered on each interface, as a result of ATM Cell Protocol Monitoring.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorEntry.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorEntry
atmfM4CellProtoErrorEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Cell Protocol Monitoring Error Log table. Each ATM interface (UNI, BICI, BISSI) automatically has an entry in this table associated with it for each error that has occurred since agent start-up.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorCode.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorCode
atmfM4CellProtoErrorCode.description: Indicates the type of error for which this entry contains information. The range and interpretation of this error code value is left up to the individual agent implementor.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorTime.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorTime
atmfM4CellProtoErrorTime.description: Value of sysUpTime when the error occurred.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorReason.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorReason
atmfM4CellProtoErrorReason.description: The cell header abnormality type: the reason for discarding the ATM cell (i.e., unassigned VPI/VCI value or VPI/VCI value out of range).

atmfM4CellProtoErrorVpi.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorVpi
atmfM4CellProtoErrorVpi.description: The VPI value of the discarded cell.

atmfM4CellProtoErrorVci.name: atmfM4CellProtoErrorVci
atmfM4CellProtoErrorVci.description: The VCI value of the discarded cell.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrDiscardedClp0.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrDiscardedClp0
atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrDiscardedClp0.description: The number of discarded CLP=0 cells due to CLP=0 only UPC/NPC policing. This object shall be present only if CLP=0 traffic is separately policed.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedCells.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedCells
atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedCells.description: The number of cells that have been successfully passed by the combined CLP=0 and CLP=1 UPC/NPC policing.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedClp0.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedClp0
atmfM4VcUpcNpcCurrPassedClp0.description: The number of CLP=0 cells that have been successfully passed by the CLP=0 UPC/NPC policing. This object shall be present only if CLP=0 traffic is separately policed.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistTable.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistTable
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 UPC/NPC Disagreement Monitoring History Data table for VCL termination points. This table maintains per-interface statistics for previous fifteen-minute intervals.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistEntry.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistEntry
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 UPC/NPC Disagreement Monitoring History Data table for VCL termination points. Each VCL Termination Point automatically has an entry in this table associated with it.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistIndex.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistIndex
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistIndex.description: A number between 1 and 96, which identifies the interval for which the set of statistics in this entry was collected. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSuspect.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSuspect
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSuspect.description: If true, the statistics in this entry may be unreliable.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistElapsedTime.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistElapsedTime
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistElapsedTime.description: Amount of time, measured in units of 0.01 second, that statistics for this entry (the current interval) have been counted.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSupprIntvls.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSupprIntvls
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistSupprIntvls.description: This attribute is non-zero only if the ATM NE is suppressing UPC/NPC Disagreement Monitoring History Data entry creation when the current interval terminates with 'all-zeroes' performance measurements. When non-zero, this attribute represents the number of 'all-zeroes' intervals that were suppressed immediately prior to this 'non-all-zeroes' history interval. Note that the suppression of 'all-zeroes' intervals is controlled by the atmfM4NeSuppressZeroStats object.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedCells.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedCells
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedCells.description: The number of discarded cells due to combined CLP=0 and CLP=1 UPC/NPC policing.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedClp0.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedClp0
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistDiscardedClp0.description: The number of discarded CLP=0 cells due to CLP=0 only UPC/NPC policing. This object shall be present only if CLP=0 traffic is separately policed.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedCells.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedCells
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedCells.description: The number of cells that have been successfully passed by the combined CLP=0 and CLP=1 UPC/NPC policing.

atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedClp0.name: atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedClp0
atmfM4VcUpcNpcHistPassedClp0.description: The number of CLP=0 cells that have been successfully passed by the CLP=0 UPC/NPC policing. This object shall be present only if CLP=0 traffic is separately policed.

atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSeg.name: atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSeg
atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSeg.description: This identifies an OAM Loopback Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using a segment OAM cell. The test type must have appended to it a code that uniquely identifies an intermediate point responsible for looping back the cell. If this is absent, the loopback is performed at the end of the segment or connection. E.g., the OID { atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSeg 5 } identifies that the loopback should be performed at the intermediate point labeled 5.

atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackE2E.name: atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackE2E
atmfM4TestOAMLoopbackE2E.description: This identifies an OAM Loopback Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using an end-to-end OAM cell.

atmfM4VpTestTable.name: atmfM4VpTestTable
atmfM4VpTestTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VP Termination Point Test table. This table allows tests to be run on VPL and VPC termination points. The operation of this table is entirely analogous to that of the ifTestTable in RFC 1573 (which was later deprecated in RFC 2233), except that the indexes into this table are different.

atmfM4VpTestEntry.name: atmfM4VpTestEntry
atmfM4VpTestEntry.description: An entry containing objects for invoking tests on a VPL or VPC termination point.

atmfM4VpTestObject.name: atmfM4VpTestObject
atmfM4VpTestObject.description: Specifies whether the test applies to the VPL termination point with the specified VPI, or the VPC termination point.

atmfM4VpTestId.name: atmfM4VpTestId
atmfM4VpTestId.description: This object identifies the current invocation of the interface's test.

atmfM4VpTestStatus.name: atmfM4VpTestStatus
atmfM4VpTestStatus.description: This object indicates whether or not some manager currently has the necessary 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this interface. A write to this object is only successful when it changes its value from 'notInUse(1)' to 'inUse(2)'. After completion of a test, the agent resets the value back to 'notInUse(1)'.

atmfM4VpTestType.name: atmfM4VpTestType
atmfM4VpTestType.description: A control variable used to start and stop operator- initiated interface tests. Most OBJECT IDENTIFIER values assigned to tests are defined elsewhere, in association with specific types of interface. However, this document assigns a value for a full- duplex loopback test, and defines the special meanings of the subject identifier: noTest OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } When the value noTest is written to this object, no action is taken unless a test is in progress, in which case the test is aborted. Writing any other value to this object is only valid when no test is currently in progress, in which case the indicated test is initiated. When read, this object always returns the most recent value that atmfM4VpTestType was set to. If it has not been set since the last initialization of the network management subsystem on the agent, a value of noTest is returned.

atmfM4VpTestResult.name: atmfM4VpTestResult
atmfM4VpTestResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested test, or the value none(1) if no tests have been requested since the last reset. Note that this facility provides no provision for saving the results of one test when starting another, as could be required if used by multiple managers concurrently.

atmfM4VpTestCode.name: atmfM4VpTestCode
atmfM4VpTestCode.description: This object contains a code which contains more specific information on the test result, for example an error-code after a failed test. Error codes and other values this object may take are specific to the type of interface and/or test. The value may have the semantics of either the AutonomousType or RowPointer textual conventions as defined in RFC 1903 [15]. The identifier: testCodeUnknown OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is defined for use if no additional result code is available.

atmfM4VpTestOwner.name: atmfM4VpTestOwner
atmfM4VpTestOwner.description: The entity which currently has the 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this interface.

atmfM4VcTestTable.name: atmfM4VcTestTable
atmfM4VcTestTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 VC Termination Point Test table. This table allows tests to be run on VCL and VCC termination points. The operation of this table is entirely analogous to that of the ifTestTable in RFC 1573 (which was later deprecated in RFC 2233), except that the indexes into this table are different.

atmfM4VcTestEntry.name: atmfM4VcTestEntry
atmfM4VcTestEntry.description: An entry containing objects for invoking tests on a VCL or VCC termination point.

atmfM4VcTestObject.name: atmfM4VcTestObject
atmfM4VcTestObject.description: Specifies whether the test applies to the VCL termination point with the specified VPI and VCI values, or to the VCC termination point.

atmfM4VcTestId.name: atmfM4VcTestId
atmfM4VcTestId.description: This object identifies the current invocation of the interface's test.

atmfM4VcTestStatus.name: atmfM4VcTestStatus
atmfM4VcTestStatus.description: This object indicates whether or not some manager currently has the necessary 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this interface. A write to this object is only successful when it changes its value from 'notInUse(1)' to 'inUse(2)'. After completion of a test, the agent resets the value back to 'notInUse(1)'.

atmfM4VcTestType.name: atmfM4VcTestType
atmfM4VcTestType.description: A control variable used to start and stop operator- initiated interface tests. Most OBJECT IDENTIFIER values assigned to tests are defined elsewhere, in association with specific types of interface. However, this document assigns a value for a full- duplex loopback test, and defines the special meanings of the subject identifier: noTest OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } When the value noTest is written to this object, no action is taken unless a test is in progress, in which case the test is aborted. Writing any other value to this object is only valid when no test is currently in progress, in which case the indicated test is initiated. When read, this object always returns the most recent value that atmfM4VcTestType was set to. If it has not been set since the last initialization of the network management subsystem on the agent, a value of noTest is returned.

atmfM4VcTestResult.name: atmfM4VcTestResult
atmfM4VcTestResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested test, or the value none(1) if no tests have been requested since the last reset. Note that this facility provides no provision for saving the results of one test when starting another, as could be required if used by multiple managers concurrently.

atmfM4VcTestCode.name: atmfM4VcTestCode
atmfM4VcTestCode.description: This object contains a code which contains more specific information on the test result, for example an error-code after a failed test. Error codes and other values this object may take are specific to the type of interface and/or test. The value may have the semantics of either the AutonomousType or RowPointer textual conventions as defined in RFC 1903 [15]. The identifier: testCodeUnknown OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is defined for use if no additional result code is available.

atmfM4VcTestOwner.name: atmfM4VcTestOwner
atmfM4VcTestOwner.description: The entity which currently has the 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this termination point.

atmfM4EquipTable.name: atmfM4EquipTable
atmfM4EquipTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Equipment table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable.

atmfM4EquipEntry.name: atmfM4EquipEntry
atmfM4EquipEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Equipment table. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment within the ATM NE that neither is nor accepts a replaceable plug-in unit.

atmfM4EquipAdminStatus.name: atmfM4EquipAdminStatus
atmfM4EquipAdminStatus.description: Used by the administrator to lock and unlock the object.

atmfM4EquipLocation.name: atmfM4EquipLocation
atmfM4EquipLocation.description: The specific or general location of the component.

atmfM4EquipOperStatus.name: atmfM4EquipOperStatus
atmfM4EquipOperStatus.description: This attributes identifies whether or not the component is capable of performing its normal functions.

atmfM4EquipUserLabel.name: atmfM4EquipUserLabel
atmfM4EquipUserLabel.description: A user-friendly name for the piece of equipment. The default value of this object is the null string.

atmfM4EquipAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4EquipAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4EquipAlarmSeverityIndex.description: An index into the alarm severity profile table, specifying the severity assignments for M4 alarms reported for this component. The default value of this object is zero.

atmfM4EquipHolderTable.name: atmfM4EquipHolderTable
atmfM4EquipHolderTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Equipment Holder table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable.

atmfM4EquipHolderEntry.name: atmfM4EquipHolderEntry
atmfM4EquipHolderEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Equipment Holder table. Each entry of this table represents a component within the ATM NE that accepts a replaceable plug-in unit.

atmfM4EquipHolderAcceptableTypes.name: atmfM4EquipHolderAcceptableTypes
atmfM4EquipHolderAcceptableTypes.description: The types of plug-in units that can be supported by the slot, separated by newline characters. This attribute shall be present only when the Equipment Holder represents a slot.

atmfM4EquipHolderSlotStatus.name: atmfM4EquipHolderSlotStatus
atmfM4EquipHolderSlotStatus.description: This attributes identifies whether or not a plug-in unit is present in the slot. This attribute shall be present only when the Equipment Holder represents a slot.

atmfM4EquipHolderSwLoad.name: atmfM4EquipHolderSwLoad
atmfM4EquipHolderSwLoad.description: An index into the installed software table, specifying the software that is to be loaded into the plug-in unit whenever an automatic reload of software is needed. This attribute shall be present only when the Equipment Holder represents a slot.

atmfM4PlugInUnitTable.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitTable
atmfM4PlugInUnitTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Plug-In Unit table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable.

atmfM4PlugInUnitEntry.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitEntry
atmfM4PlugInUnitEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Plug-In Unit table. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment within the ATM NE that is inserted into and removed from an Equipment Holder.

atmfM4PlugInUnitAdminStatus.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitAdminStatus
atmfM4PlugInUnitAdminStatus.description: Used by the administrator to lock and unlock the object.

atmfM4PlugInUnitAvailStatus.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitAvailStatus
atmfM4PlugInUnitAvailStatus.description: Provides further information regarding the state of the component.

atmfM4PlugInUnitOperStatus.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitOperStatus
atmfM4PlugInUnitOperStatus.description: This attributes identifies whether or not the component is capable of performing its normal functions.

atmfM4PlugInUnitAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4PlugInUnitAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4PlugInUnitAlarmSeverityIndex.description: An index into the alarm severity profile table, specifying the severity assignments for M4 alarms reported for this component. The default value of this object is zero.

atmfM4HwRunningSwTable.name: atmfM4HwRunningSwTable
atmfM4HwRunningSwTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Hardware Unit/Running Software relationship table. This table describes the software that is running on each hardware unit in the ATM NE.

atmfM4HwRunningSwEntry.name: atmfM4HwRunningSwEntry
atmfM4HwRunningSwEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Hardware Unit/Running Software relationship table. Each entry of this table identifies an entry in the entPhysicalTable and one in the hrSWRunTable.

atmfM4HwRunningSwHwIndex.name: atmfM4HwRunningSwHwIndex
atmfM4HwRunningSwHwIndex.description: The index, in the entPhysicalTable, of the containing hardware unit in this pair.

atmfM4HwRunningSwIndex.name: atmfM4HwRunningSwIndex
atmfM4HwRunningSwIndex.description: A unique number within the context of the containing hardware unit.

atmfM4HwRunningSwSwIndex.name: atmfM4HwRunningSwSwIndex
atmfM4HwRunningSwSwIndex.description: The index, in the hrSWRunTable, of the software product represented by this entry.

atmfM4HwInstalledSwTable.name: atmfM4HwInstalledSwTable
atmfM4HwInstalledSwTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Hardware Unit/Installed Software relationship table. This table describes the software that is installed on each hardware unit in the ATM NE.

atmfM4HwInstalledSwEntry.name: atmfM4HwInstalledSwEntry
atmfM4HwInstalledSwEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Forum M4 Hardware Unit/Installed Software relationship table. Each entry of this table identifies an entry in the entPhysicalTable and one in the hrSWInstalledTable.

atmfM4HwInstalledSwHwIndex.name: atmfM4HwInstalledSwHwIndex
atmfM4HwInstalledSwHwIndex.description: The index, in the entPhysicalTable, of the containing physical entity in this pair.

atmfM4HwInstalledSwIndex.name: atmfM4HwInstalledSwIndex
atmfM4HwInstalledSwIndex.description: A unique number within the context of the containing hardware unit.

atmfM4HwInstalledSwSwIndex.name: atmfM4HwInstalledSwSwIndex
atmfM4HwInstalledSwSwIndex.description: The index, in the hrSWInstalledTable, of the software product represented by this entry.

atmfM4HwSwAlarmSeverityIndex.name: atmfM4HwSwAlarmSeverityIndex
atmfM4HwSwAlarmSeverityIndex.description: An index into the alarm severity profile table, specifying the severity assignments for M4 alarms reported for this piece of software installed on the hardware unit. The default value of this object is zero.

AtmfM4AlarmLogSeverity.name: AtmfM4AlarmLogSeverity
AtmfM4AlarmLogSeverity.description: The value of this object identifies the severity of an alarm in the log, including 'cleared'.

AtmfM4AlarmSeverity.name: AtmfM4AlarmSeverity
AtmfM4AlarmSeverity.description: The value of this object identifies the severity of an alarm that has occurred. (Note that there is no value corresponding to 'cleared'.)

atmfM4AlarmSevDefault.name: atmfM4AlarmSevDefault
atmfM4AlarmSevDefault.description: The default severity value used for new profile index/trap ID pairs that have not yet been modified. This value is also used whenever an object's alarm severity profile index is set to 0. The default value of this object is minor(3).

atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndexNext.name: atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndexNext
atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndex when creating entries in the atmfM4AlarmSevProfileTable. The value -1 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the index value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index (or -1).

atmfM4AlarmSevProfileTable.name: atmfM4AlarmSevProfileTable
atmfM4AlarmSevProfileTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 alarm severity profile table. This table specifies which profiles exist. Creating or deleting an entry in this table automatically creates or deletes the corresponding entries in the atmfM4AlarmSeverityTable.

atmfM4AlarmSevProfileEntry.name: atmfM4AlarmSevProfileEntry
atmfM4AlarmSevProfileEntry.description: A group of severities, one for each alarm type in the communications alarm group.

atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndex.name: atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndex
atmfM4AlarmSevProfileIndex.description: A number identifying this alarm severity profile.

atmfM4AlarmSevProfileRowStatus.name: atmfM4AlarmSevProfileRowStatus
atmfM4AlarmSevProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

atmfM4AlarmSevTable.name: atmfM4AlarmSevTable
atmfM4AlarmSevTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 alarm severity table. This table associates profile index and trap ID pairs with severities to be used for M4 alarm traps that have occurred. (Note that this table does not apply to cleared alarms.)

atmfM4AlarmSevEntry.name: atmfM4AlarmSevEntry
atmfM4AlarmSevEntry.description: An entry in this table associates an alarm severity profile index/trap ID pair with a severity. Deleting a particular profile's row in the alarm severity profile table deletes all rows in this table with the same profile index. Conceptually, rows corresponding to all possible trap ID's are created in this table when a new alarm severity profile is created, but the agent will return a default value except for those few traps for which values have been set.

atmfM4AlarmSevTrapId.name: atmfM4AlarmSevTrapId
atmfM4AlarmSevTrapId.description: The ID of the trap type to which this entry applies.

atmfM4AlarmSeverity.name: atmfM4AlarmSeverity
atmfM4AlarmSeverity.description: The severity to be used for this trap type when the TrapId is selected. If no value for this object has ever been set since the corresponding profile was created, the agent should return the value of the object atmfM4AlarmSevDefault.

atmfM4ForwardAllTraps.name: atmfM4ForwardAllTraps
atmfM4ForwardAllTraps.description: This is used as the value of the object atmfM4ForwardedTrapObject when traps from all objects are to be forwarded, or when there is only one object of the type that forwards the specified trap type.

atmfM4TrapForwardingTable.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingTable
atmfM4TrapForwardingTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Trap forwarding discriminator table. This table specifies which traps will be sent to which management system.

atmfM4TrapForwardingEntry.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingEntry
atmfM4TrapForwardingEntry.description: Information about a group of traps to be sent to a particular IP address. A new entry must have values for all attributes that do not have default values before its RowStatus column can be set to active(1).

atmfM4TrapForwardingIndex.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingIndex
atmfM4TrapForwardingIndex.description: A unique number identifying the table entry.

atmfM4TrapForwardingDest.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingDest
atmfM4TrapForwardingDest.description: The IP address to which traps identified by this table entry should be sent.

atmfM4ForwardedTrapId.name: atmfM4ForwardedTrapId
atmfM4ForwardedTrapId.description: The ID of the trap type to which this entry applies.

atmfM4ForwardedTrapObject.name: atmfM4ForwardedTrapObject
atmfM4ForwardedTrapObject.description: The object to which this entry applies. By convention, this is the name of the first object in the row in the table referenced. The special value { 0 0 } indicates that traps of this type from all objects of the type that can generate it. It should also be used when traps from the ATM NE are to be specified.

atmfM4TrapForwardingPort.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingPort
atmfM4TrapForwardingPort.description: The UDP port on the specified management system to which traps identified by this entry should be sent.

atmfM4LowestForwardedSeverity.name: atmfM4LowestForwardedSeverity
atmfM4LowestForwardedSeverity.description: The lowest severity of traps of this type from the specified object that should be sent to this address. This object has significance only if the trap type specified has a severity associated with it.

atmfM4ForwardedIndeterminate.name: atmfM4ForwardedIndeterminate
atmfM4ForwardedIndeterminate.description: When this object has the value TRUE, traps with indeterminate severity will be forwarded to the specified event. This object has significance only if the trap type specified has a severity associated with it.

atmfM4TrapForwardingRowStatus.name: atmfM4TrapForwardingRowStatus
atmfM4TrapForwardingRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

atmfM4TrapLogTable.name: atmfM4TrapLogTable
atmfM4TrapLogTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Trap Agent log table. This table defines the trap logs currently maintained by the agent. The management system creates entries in this table to specify which types of traps, from which ATM network elements, should be logged. Deleting an entry in this table deletes all entries in the corresponding log.

atmfM4TrapLogEntry.name: atmfM4TrapLogEntry
atmfM4TrapLogEntry.description: Information about a single trap log.

atmfM4TrapLogSrc.name: atmfM4TrapLogSrc
atmfM4TrapLogSrc.description: The IP address of the SNMP agent whose traps are stored in this log.

atmfM4TrapLogType.name: atmfM4TrapLogType
atmfM4TrapLogType.description: The type of traps stored in this log.

atmfM4TrapLogAdminStatus.name: atmfM4TrapLogAdminStatus
atmfM4TrapLogAdminStatus.description: The management system uses this object to stop and start the operations of this object.

atmfM4TrapLogOperStatus.name: atmfM4TrapLogOperStatus
atmfM4TrapLogOperStatus.description: Indicates whether or not the log is capable of performing its normal operations.

atmfM4TrapLogFullAction.name: atmfM4TrapLogFullAction
atmfM4TrapLogFullAction.description: Indicates the action that should be performed when no more log entries can be created due to a log-full condition. If the value of this object is wrap(2), each new log entry will cause the deletion of the oldest entry still in the log, for as long as the log is still full.

atmfM4TrapLogRowStatus.name: atmfM4TrapLogRowStatus
atmfM4TrapLogRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

atmfM4LoggedTrapTable.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapTable
atmfM4LoggedTrapTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Trap Agent logged trap table. This table is used to maintain the traps logged.

atmfM4LoggedTrapEntry.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapEntry
atmfM4LoggedTrapEntry.description: Information about a single trap in the log. Entries in this table are created automatically but can be deleted by the management system. Entries that represent 'alarm' log types are augmented by the atmfM4LoggedAlarmEntry table.

atmfM4LoggedTrapIndex.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapIndex
atmfM4LoggedTrapIndex.description: A unique number identifying this entry in the log. When the maximum value for this object has been reached, it will wrap around to 0.

atmfM4LoggedTrapTime.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapTime
atmfM4LoggedTrapTime.description: The time at which this trap was logged.

atmfM4LoggedTrapID.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapID
atmfM4LoggedTrapID.description: The type of trap to which this entry applies. Together with the logged trap ID object, this object specifies the entity to which this logged trap referred.

atmfM4LoggedTrapObject.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapObject
atmfM4LoggedTrapObject.description: The object to which this entry applies. By convention, this is the name of the first object in the row in the table referenced. Together with the logged trap ID object, this object specifies the entity to which this logged trap referred. The special value { 0 0 } indicates that the trap refers to the ATM NE entity itself.

atmfM4LoggedTrapRowStatus.name: atmfM4LoggedTrapRowStatus
atmfM4LoggedTrapRowStatus.description: This object is used to delete an existing row in the table. Note that the only value to which a management system can set this object is destroy(6).

atmfM4LoggedAlarmTable.name: atmfM4LoggedAlarmTable
atmfM4LoggedAlarmTable.description: The ATM Forum M4 Trap Agent logged alarm trap table. This table is used to maintain extra information for logged traps that represent alarm types.

atmfM4LoggedAlarmEntry.name: atmfM4LoggedAlarmEntry
atmfM4LoggedAlarmEntry.description: Information about the alarm-specific attributes of a single trap in the log.

atmfM4LoggedAlarmSeverity.name: atmfM4LoggedAlarmSeverity
atmfM4LoggedAlarmSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the alarm, as specified by the agent that generated it.

atmfM4LoggedAlarmBackedUp.name: atmfM4LoggedAlarmBackedUp
atmfM4LoggedAlarmBackedUp.description: If the value of this object is true, the agent reported in this trap that the failed object had been backed up. This object is only present if it was included in the alarm trap corresponding to this log entry.

atmfM4LoggedAlarmBUObject.name: atmfM4LoggedAlarmBUObject
